You feel the vibrations of each heavy step move up your legs and into your ass, causing it to jiggle. Finally you reach the floor below the high chambers, which is where you live. On this floor is where the low chambers are located. The low chambers are where the advisers of the kingdom live, such as the viceroy or royal engineer. You don’t spend any time on this level of the tower, because, well, you have no reason to. You take a moment to catch your breath on the small landing before continuing your journey. You feel your stomach rumble, it seems all this moving around has awoken your hunger. You hope that Mother and Father don’t take too long, you’d like to get some food in your fat gut sooner rather than later. You once again continue your journey down the stairs. You’ve always hated the long winding steps from the high chambers down to the lower floors of the keep, though you’ve also always hated anything that involves too much walking. Eventually you reach the bottom of the stairs, they lead into a wide hallway that has a long rug down the center and some decorations on the walls. For a hallway it's a pretty good hallway, though you think it would definitely have some improvements, namely some benches. You start once more walking towards the courtyard. It takes you a few minutes of waddling down the hallway but eventually you come to another stairwell. It’s a much shorter stairwell, with it only descending one floor. From there it's only a little further to the keep’s entrance, which leads out to the courtyard.As you near the doors to the courtyard the two guards open the large, heavy doors for you. Walking out into the courtyard you see the majority of the guard assembled. Their armor and helmets glimmering in the sunlight. Speaking of sunlight, it's a nice sunny day. The birds are singing, flowers are blooming, on days like this, girls like you should be… having a nice picnic, not standing around awaiting the arrival of your parents. As the seconds turn into minutes you start to grow bored. You start to debate going back inside and eating when you hear a bellow from the gate house. “A rider approaches! It’s knight!” You hear the sound of metal stressing as the heavy grate raises open just as a single rider comes bolting through the gate. A single rider? The words echo in your head. The king and Queen's entourage consists of a dozen or more riders plus a carriage at least. A singer rider, a knight no less, merits cause for concern. The only time a knight would be sent as a messenger is if something terrible has happened. You see that it's a knight, he's riding a beautiful black horse. His armor glimmers in the light. As he nears however the sight of a knight in shining armor is quickly shattered as you notice several arrow shafts sticking out of the body of his stead. You now notice the horse barely keeping its breakneck pace as it leaves a trail of blood behind itself. The knight is in a similar state to his horse. You see his armor has been dented, arrow shafts are sticking out in the gaps in his armor, one in his shoulder and another in the elbow joint. His arm handing uselessly down to his side as his other arm holds the reins of his horse firmly, keeping it going only through will and duty alone. He comes to a stop, skidding in front of you. His horse wobbles, lets out a small neigh, knowing his final task has been completed, before collapsing. The knight, not having the energy to move, goes down with his horse. Guards run over, removing the man's helmet and giving him some water, which he promptly spits out. You hear him croak something, one of the guards nods. “Your highness, he wishes to speak to you.” You anxiously walk over to hear what the mortality wounded man has to say. As you near you can hear him wheezing, he hasn’t got long you think to yourself. You lean down to better hear him as he starts to gently speak, his voice no more than a whisper. “King… Queen… dead… bandits… south… only survivor… me… we… we… failed.” The last word leaves his mouth with a shudder, as if the word itself deals him a final mortal blow. He shudders, takes one last shallow breath before his head collapses and his body goes limp. You know that he's gone. You take a shaky step back, you feel your knees go out as you collapse to the ground. Your vision is blinded by tears, all you can think is that you have lost your mother and father. You feel yourself picked up and guided into the keep, a dozen faces go past your vision, their words melt together. You are consumed by grief. <<case 3 4>> Now fully dressed, you decide that it's now time to go down stairs to meet your parents. [[Start your first day as Queen|Bedroom]] It has been two weeks since you got the news of your parents murder, in that time you have grieved their loss, become queen and given them a proper burial. You’ve also received more news of their murder in this time. Shortly after the knight brought you the news of their murder a force was sent out to investigate. They found the king and Queen's carriage, it was covered in arrows and surrounded by the dozen or so bodies of their royal guard. Inside the carriage the king and queens bodies were nowhere to be found. The king's body was eventually found resting near one of the wheels of the carriage; he wasn’t recognised at first due to the sheer volume of the cuts, stabs and arrow wounds that covered his body, leaving his clothes torn and his body mutilated. He died fighting alongside his men before he was struck down. The Queen was found a few hundred yards away. It seemed that she had managed to escape the initial attack along with her handmaiden. However her handmaiden had taken an arrow to the leg, which slowed her down. When their bodies were found it looks like the queen and her handmaiden attempted to hide. It seems they were found and slaughtered; their bodies not touched by blade, insead when they were found hiding in a ditch they were simply shot with a dozen or so arrows. The deaths of both of your parents was executed with such hate and malice you have to wonder who could have done such a thing. It’s unusual for a king or Queen to die or be assassinated, especially once loved as much as your parents. When this news was brought back to you all you felt was rage and fury at what happened. You wanted to see the people who had done this burn. And you would have your revenge now that you’re queen. After two weeks of grieving, coronations and learning the bare minimum you feel ready to actually start being the Queen, but before that you should get a good night's rest.
